2011-08-25 17:04 -0400  djerius  <djerius@cfa.harvard.edu>  (a5f2eb7c027a)

	* doc/validate.args.pod, tests/object.lua, tests/positional.lua,
	validate/args.lua:
	nil positional parameters are now by default not allowed.

	The default behavior was to allow nil positional arguments. This is
	inconsistent with the behavior for table arguments (e.g., optional
	defaults to false), and caused confusion.

	The new default behavior is that positional arguments may not be
	nil. A new specification, allow_nil, may be used to indicate that
	nil values are permitted. The not_nil specification is now
	redundant and deprecated.

