2011-06-17 11:37 -0400  djerius  <djerius@cfa.harvard.edu>  (e912d278bbab)

	* validate/args.lua:
	carry name with parameters when traversing spec tree

	previously, as the spec tree was navigated any given function was
	ignorant of the name of the spec's parent variable; it knew only the
	children. While this approach obviated passing extra name
	information along, it made it impossible to pass a fully qualified
	name to any callbacks.

	the full name is now passed along as a Name object containing an
	ordered list of the components in a variable name as well as the
	index of the last valid component. The name object is cloned at each
	level; the new object gets an independent copy of the index, but
	shares the same list of names as its parent. This is more efficient
	than copying the list, and because the parent's index is untouched
	removes the need to independently increment and decrement the index
	as levels in the tree are traversed.

